1
00:00:01,419 --> 00:00:02,920
Your papa and I…

2
00:00:03,003 --> 00:00:03,963
We've been separated.

3
00:00:04,046 --> 00:00:08,175
Did you even consider
how we'd feel if you separated?

4
00:00:08,259 --> 00:00:09,301
Yes!

5
00:00:09,385 --> 00:00:12,304
A thousand times, we did.

6
00:00:12,388 --> 00:00:14,557
That's why you were devastated
when Teacher Sam died.

7
00:00:14,640 --> 00:00:18,853
No. I don't know how to explain it to you.

8
00:00:18,936 --> 00:00:20,896
It was a good thing she died!

9
00:00:33,284 --> 00:00:34,952
I wonder if there's a way

10
00:00:35,035 --> 00:00:36,871
to know what Eli's world feels like.

11
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:45,254
I just didn't like
that the last time we talked

12
00:00:45,337 --> 00:00:47,506
would be our last goodbye.

13
00:00:47,590 --> 00:00:48,924
Bye, Sam.

14
00:00:50,593 --> 00:00:51,427
Jackie…

15
00:01:03,439 --> 00:01:05,149
You damn bastard!

16
00:01:05,232 --> 00:01:06,609
How dare you!

17
00:01:06,692 --> 00:01:08,360
You're lucky your father was there.

18
00:01:08,444 --> 00:01:09,779
You should consider yourself lucky

19
00:01:09,862 --> 00:01:12,156
my father hasn't gotten hold
of Ms. Ignacio's phone.

20
00:01:44,647 --> 00:01:45,648
Pia.

21
00:01:48,818 --> 00:01:49,652
Pia!

22
00:02:05,584 --> 00:02:06,669
Are you okay?

23
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:17,304
I don't know what's okay anymore.

24
00:04:23,305 --> 00:04:24,723
You drew this?

25
00:04:44,910 --> 00:04:47,079
Were you…

26
00:04:47,162 --> 00:04:52,668
at the lighthouse

27
00:04:52,751 --> 00:04:54,336
that night?

28
00:04:57,089 --> 00:04:58,507
Were you?

29
00:05:04,221 --> 00:05:06,432
Just tell me the truth.

30
00:05:08,976 --> 00:05:10,227
Just tell me.

31
00:05:12,271 --> 00:05:13,564
I want to be alone!

32
00:05:55,856 --> 00:05:56,857
Jackie.

33
00:05:58,275 --> 00:05:59,276
Where's Pia?

34
00:06:03,655 --> 00:06:05,949
-She's not in her room?
-No.

35
00:06:06,033 --> 00:06:08,243
-How about Matteo's?
-She isn't there either.

36
00:06:08,327 --> 00:06:10,204
-In the bathroom?
-No luck.

37
00:06:31,558 --> 00:06:33,268
What exactly happened?

38
00:06:35,479 --> 00:06:37,231
I'm not ready to talk about it yet.

39
00:06:40,943 --> 00:06:42,820
But if I had a choice,

40
00:06:44,947 --> 00:06:46,949
I wouldn't go home right now.

41
00:06:50,911 --> 00:06:52,746
Do you know what I hate the most?

42
00:06:54,998 --> 00:06:56,291
Liars.

43
00:06:57,876 --> 00:07:00,546
That's what Mama and Papa taught me.

44
00:07:01,171 --> 00:07:02,589
To be honest

45
00:07:03,841 --> 00:07:06,176
and unafraid to tell the truth.

46
00:07:08,095 --> 00:07:11,473
And yet, all this time,
they were the ones doing it.

47
00:07:14,601 --> 00:07:16,895
They were the ones lying to us.

48
00:07:26,655 --> 00:07:30,784
They probably just didn't want
to hurt you.

49
00:07:30,868 --> 00:07:33,370
That's why they kept it secret,

50
00:07:34,246 --> 00:07:36,832
whatever it was they were hiding.

51
00:07:39,835 --> 00:07:42,838
I'd rather face the painful truth…

52
00:07:44,882 --> 00:07:48,260
than go on believing
that everything was fine

53
00:07:48,343 --> 00:07:49,970
when it actually wasn't.

54
00:07:51,763 --> 00:07:53,307
They knew that themselves.

55
00:07:54,099 --> 00:07:56,894
They couldn't hide it
for the rest of their lives.

56
00:08:00,063 --> 00:08:01,690
And isn't it more painful

57
00:08:02,399 --> 00:08:05,652
when you find out everything
you believed was a lie?

58
00:08:54,243 --> 00:08:56,036
She's not picking up.

59
00:08:56,119 --> 00:08:57,120
Call her again.

60
00:08:58,789 --> 00:08:59,623
Matt.

61
00:09:00,123 --> 00:09:00,958
Could--

62
00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:04,127
Matteo, could you please try?

63
00:09:26,066 --> 00:09:26,942
Excuse me.

64
00:09:34,950 --> 00:09:35,784
Matteo.

65
00:09:35,867 --> 00:09:37,286
Pia?

66
00:09:37,369 --> 00:09:38,578
Pia, where are you?

67
00:09:39,830 --> 00:09:41,707
I'm outside, getting some air.

68
00:09:42,374 --> 00:09:43,834
This is my last bottle.

69
00:09:43,917 --> 00:09:45,627
I don't even have
any allowance left for tomorrow.

70
00:09:45,711 --> 00:09:47,796
-You're such a loser.
-Pia…

71
00:09:48,964 --> 00:09:50,924
Will you come home now, please?

72
00:09:51,008 --> 00:09:53,677
Pia, sweetie.
Where are you? I'll pick you up.

73
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:54,761
Can you not?

74
00:09:55,387 --> 00:09:57,097
Leave me alone.

75
00:09:57,180 --> 00:09:59,266
Just this once. Please.

76
00:09:59,349 --> 00:10:02,102
Alone? It sounds like
you're out drinking, Pia.

77
00:10:08,358 --> 00:10:10,986
I guess lying runs in the family.

78
00:10:24,166 --> 00:10:25,250
I'll look for her myself.

79
00:10:28,211 --> 00:10:29,171
I'll go with him.

80
00:10:32,716 --> 00:10:34,051
You can go home if you want.

81
00:10:34,926 --> 00:10:36,261
No way I'm leaving you.

82
00:10:36,345 --> 00:10:37,971
I'd feel guilty if you went
around picking fights.

83
00:10:38,055 --> 00:10:39,014
Cheers!

84
00:10:39,973 --> 00:10:42,809
Thanks, doofus. I really thought
you were concerned about me.

85
00:10:48,982 --> 00:10:50,233
What does alcohol taste like?

86
00:10:50,901 --> 00:10:52,569
You haven't tried it?

87
00:10:53,779 --> 00:10:54,780
Not allowed.

88
00:10:55,781 --> 00:10:58,241
Mama and Papa would be furious if I did.

89
00:11:10,253 --> 00:11:12,005
Where are you-- Hey!

90
00:11:13,757 --> 00:11:14,591
Pia!

91
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:17,260
Pia!

92
00:13:22,677 --> 00:13:24,387
You just had to ruin it, didn't you?

93
00:13:30,310 --> 00:13:31,144
Nothing.

94
00:13:32,646 --> 00:13:34,481
What do you mean "nothing"?

95
00:13:39,194 --> 00:13:40,654
I had a plan.

96
00:13:43,198 --> 00:13:44,616
But right now…

97
00:13:50,705 --> 00:13:52,541
I don't know anymore.

98
00:13:55,794 --> 00:13:57,170
Why?

99
00:13:57,254 --> 00:13:58,630
Tell me.

100
00:13:59,381 --> 00:14:02,133
Because things will fall apart.

101
00:14:07,556 --> 00:14:09,307
People will get hurt.

102
00:14:12,769 --> 00:14:14,187
You're confusing me.

103
00:14:14,771 --> 00:14:16,648
I don't get you.
You're all over the place.

104
00:14:16,731 --> 00:14:18,400
What, are you drunk?

105
00:14:30,537 --> 00:14:32,038
Just go home for now.

106
00:14:33,582 --> 00:14:35,375
Eli might be worried.

107
00:14:41,464 --> 00:14:42,841
Come on.

108
00:14:47,262 --> 00:14:48,305
Let's go.

109
00:14:49,514 --> 00:14:50,682
Can you walk?

110
00:14:54,144 --> 00:14:55,687
-Where's the car?
-Jeez.

111
00:15:00,275 --> 00:15:01,610
Hey, hey, hey.

112
00:15:12,579 --> 00:15:13,830
Pia!

113
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:17,959
-Dad!
-Open the door.

114
00:15:18,043 --> 00:15:20,128
-Pia, come on.
-Get in the car!

115
00:15:20,211 --> 00:15:21,087
What the hell!

116
00:15:22,047 --> 00:15:24,174
Why are you making her drink, you bastard?

117
00:15:24,257 --> 00:15:26,259
I didn't make her drink, sir.
She wanted to.

118
00:15:26,343 --> 00:15:28,970
And don't blame me.

119
00:15:29,054 --> 00:15:31,473
You're the reason she's like that now.

120
00:15:36,811 --> 00:15:37,979
Give me that!

121
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:41,608
Mr. Carpio!

122
00:15:43,485 --> 00:15:45,153
What's your problem with my son?

123
00:15:45,236 --> 00:15:46,321
Sir! Sir!

124
00:15:46,404 --> 00:15:47,781
Give me a ride!

125
00:15:50,784 --> 00:15:52,077
Talk to your son.

126
00:15:53,328 --> 00:15:54,537
Tell him to stay away from my daughter.

127
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:30,990
Pia?

128
00:16:33,827 --> 00:16:35,286
What happened?

129
00:16:36,746 --> 00:16:38,164
-Hey!
-Pia.

130
00:16:38,248 --> 00:16:39,416
Pia!

131
00:16:39,499 --> 00:16:40,750
-Pia, come on.
-I don't want to!

132
00:16:40,834 --> 00:16:41,668
Dear.

133
00:16:42,210 --> 00:16:43,753
Where did you find her?

134
00:16:44,421 --> 00:16:47,215
She was in town with that pest, Kyle.

135
00:16:48,174 --> 00:16:49,634
He's not a pest!

136
00:16:51,636 --> 00:16:54,013
Pests don't smell like that.

137
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:08,611
Pia, didn't I warn you about that Kyle?

138
00:17:09,779 --> 00:17:11,573
He's just going to ruin you. Look at you.

139
00:17:11,656 --> 00:17:13,533
You're drinking, you're getting drunk.

140
00:17:13,616 --> 00:17:15,452
I drank because I wanted to!

141
00:17:17,162 --> 00:17:19,205
No one taught me.

142
00:17:20,373 --> 00:17:21,833
Why does it matter?

143
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:23,710
Did someone teach you back then

144
00:17:24,502 --> 00:17:26,129
when you cheated?

145
00:17:26,212 --> 00:17:27,422
Pia.

146
00:17:28,173 --> 00:17:29,674
That's enough.

147
00:17:29,758 --> 00:17:31,509
Come on, let's go to your room.

148
00:17:31,593 --> 00:17:32,969
I'll stay with you.

149
00:17:33,553 --> 00:17:35,930
When did you start talking back like that?

150
00:17:37,599 --> 00:17:38,850
Pia, that's not you.

151
00:17:38,933 --> 00:17:41,186
You became like this because of Kyle.

152
00:17:41,269 --> 00:17:42,896
Then who is the Pia you know?

153
00:17:44,147 --> 00:17:46,065
The Pia who always says,

154
00:17:46,149 --> 00:17:47,484
"Yes, Pa!"

155
00:17:48,485 --> 00:17:49,694
"Yes, Ma!"

156
00:18:06,252 --> 00:18:08,129
You're exhausting!

157
00:18:14,052 --> 00:18:15,804
What's the point?

158
00:18:17,222 --> 00:18:20,058
There's no point in making you proud

159
00:18:20,141 --> 00:18:23,144
because there's nothing
to be proud of in this family!

160
00:18:25,897 --> 00:18:27,148
Pia…

161
00:18:27,690 --> 00:18:30,318
There's no such thing
as a perfect family, dear.

162
00:18:32,237 --> 00:18:35,156
Parents make mistakes too.

163
00:18:36,533 --> 00:18:38,952
Yes, we lied to you.

164
00:18:39,452 --> 00:18:42,622
But our love for you is real.

165
00:18:43,915 --> 00:18:46,918
And that won't change. It won't.

166
00:18:50,588 --> 00:18:52,048
Pia…

167
00:19:03,601 --> 00:19:04,978
Wait, wait, wait.

168
00:19:05,562 --> 00:19:08,439
We need a new family picture.

169
00:19:09,566 --> 00:19:11,192
A more honest one.

170
00:20:19,552 --> 00:20:23,473
Eli. Come on. Let's go home.

171
00:20:25,558 --> 00:20:26,684
Matteo!

172
00:20:26,768 --> 00:20:29,646
I'll see you tomorrow, huh, Champ? Okay?

173
00:20:29,729 --> 00:20:31,439
I'll see you.

174
00:20:48,456 --> 00:20:49,707
Let's end this.

175
00:21:06,641 --> 00:21:10,019
How was your session with Teacher Sam?

176
00:21:44,303 --> 00:21:49,308
Are you sad about Teacher Sam?

177
00:21:51,728 --> 00:21:55,690
Does she really have to leave?

178
00:21:58,401 --> 00:22:00,903
Butterflies leave

179
00:22:00,987 --> 00:22:04,157
when it's time for them to grow.

180
00:22:05,408 --> 00:22:09,078
And when they fly away,

181
00:22:09,162 --> 00:22:12,457
we have to let them go.

182
00:22:18,254 --> 00:22:21,049
I'm sorry

183
00:22:21,132 --> 00:22:24,260
you saw me and Papa fight earlier.

184
00:22:24,761 --> 00:22:29,766
You and Papa always fight.

185
00:22:31,476 --> 00:22:35,730
Don't you love Papa anymore?

186
00:22:39,067 --> 00:22:43,780
It's normal for couples to fight.

187
00:22:46,866 --> 00:22:49,952
Go to sleep.

188
00:22:50,036 --> 00:22:54,207
I'll just go somewhere,
but I'll be right back.

189
00:22:56,292 --> 00:23:01,964
What about Papa?

190
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:05,635
Can I come too?

191
00:23:05,718 --> 00:23:10,389
Don't worry, I'll find him.
No need to wait for us.

192
00:23:11,557 --> 00:23:17,188
Tomorrow's a big day, remember?

193
00:23:19,816 --> 00:23:20,817
Go to sleep.

194
00:23:35,915 --> 00:23:40,795
-I love you.
-I love you.

195
00:28:00,137 --> 00:28:00,971
Eli.

196
00:28:01,055 --> 00:28:03,391
I'll talk to him.

197
00:28:53,858 --> 00:28:57,361
I followed you that night.

198
00:29:00,739 --> 00:29:05,494
I saw you and Teacher Sam.

199
00:29:07,371 --> 00:29:09,290
You were kissing.

200
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:16,130
Friends don't kiss like that.

201
00:29:16,213 --> 00:29:20,509
No, no, no!

202
00:29:21,218 --> 00:29:25,306
I'm so sorry, son.

203
00:29:29,101 --> 00:29:35,483
But… How? Why did you follow me?

204
00:29:38,319 --> 00:29:40,654
Why didn't you tell me?

205
00:29:42,156 --> 00:29:44,325
I didn't know how.

206
00:29:45,493 --> 00:29:49,497
You know you can always talk to me.

207
00:29:50,331 --> 00:29:53,584
Tell me. Ask me anything.
I'll try to answer.

208
00:29:56,545 --> 00:29:58,297
I'm scared.

209
00:30:01,258 --> 00:30:03,511
You don't have to be.

210
00:30:09,058 --> 00:30:10,809
I pushed her.

211
00:30:12,436 --> 00:30:15,022
I killed Teacher Sam.

212
00:31:24,466 --> 00:31:26,510
What are you doing here?

213
00:31:28,762 --> 00:31:31,473
Were you there the whole time?

214
00:31:35,603 --> 00:31:36,520
Eli.

215
00:31:36,604 --> 00:31:38,272
I hate you! I hate you!

216
00:31:38,355 --> 00:31:40,608
I thought you were my friend.
You said you cared for me.

217
00:31:43,110 --> 00:31:46,530
I saw you and Mama!

218
00:31:48,574 --> 00:31:51,410
You were kissing.

219
00:31:51,493 --> 00:31:53,954
No. I'm sorry.

220
00:31:54,038 --> 00:31:55,122
I'm sorry, Eli.

221
00:31:55,205 --> 00:31:56,999
I hate you!

222
00:31:57,082 --> 00:32:01,170
Wait. No, no, no. Wait. Wait.

223
00:32:02,630 --> 00:32:04,006
Your mama,

224
00:32:04,965 --> 00:32:06,467
she'll never leave you.

225
00:32:06,550 --> 00:32:09,762
Not for me, not for anybody, never!

226
00:32:11,430 --> 00:32:13,015
Don't lie!

227
00:32:13,724 --> 00:32:15,851
I saw you!

228
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:18,312
You can't take Mama away from us!

229
00:32:18,395 --> 00:32:20,397
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

230
00:32:20,481 --> 00:32:23,901
Eli, I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.

231
00:32:23,984 --> 00:32:26,403
Please, listen to me.
Let me explain, okay?

232
00:32:26,487 --> 00:32:28,155
Let me explain, please.

233
00:32:51,845 --> 00:32:53,597
I killed Teacher Sam!

234
00:32:53,681 --> 00:32:55,766
Stop. Stop.

235
00:32:55,849 --> 00:32:57,267
Eli, stop signing.

236
00:32:59,269 --> 00:33:04,900
You didn't kill Teacher Sam.

237
00:33:10,989 --> 00:33:14,118
I pushed Teacher Sam!

238
00:33:14,201 --> 00:33:16,370
It was an accident.

239
00:33:17,913 --> 00:33:19,707
It was an accident!

240
00:33:23,043 --> 00:33:25,087
Teacher Sam died because of me.

241
00:33:25,170 --> 00:33:28,507
You didn't want that.

242
00:33:28,590 --> 00:33:31,719
Hey, look at me. Look at me.

243
00:33:32,469 --> 00:33:33,679
Look at Mama.

244
00:33:37,349 --> 00:33:41,562
It wasn't your fault.

245
00:33:42,479 --> 00:33:45,023
It wasn't your fault, Eli.

246
00:33:45,107 --> 00:33:46,316
It was me.

247
00:33:47,526 --> 00:33:51,780
Me. Me. It was me. It was my fault.

248
00:33:51,864 --> 00:33:54,450
It's Mama. It's Mama who's at fault.

249
00:33:54,533 --> 00:33:58,412
Me. It's not you. It's not your fault.

250
00:33:58,495 --> 00:34:00,080
It's not your fault!

251
00:34:00,164 --> 00:34:01,832
Shh, stop.

252
00:34:49,630 --> 00:34:51,757
Is this what Anton wanted
to get from you earlier?

253
00:34:55,052 --> 00:34:55,969
-Is this it?
-Pa, give me that.

254
00:34:57,930 --> 00:34:59,139
Answer me.

255
00:35:00,182 --> 00:35:01,600
Who owns this?

256
00:35:04,394 --> 00:35:06,230
Why were you going to throw it?

257
00:35:06,313 --> 00:35:07,147
Answer!

258
00:35:10,567 --> 00:35:12,736
Why can't you answer, huh?

259
00:35:12,820 --> 00:35:15,155
If you don't speak up,
I won't give this back to you.

260
00:35:15,239 --> 00:35:16,365
I'll have this opened.

261
00:35:17,908 --> 00:35:18,826
Pa.

262
00:35:24,498 --> 00:35:25,958
It's Sam Ignacio's.

263
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:51,275
Eli.

264
00:36:11,378 --> 00:36:14,756
It hurts right here.

265
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:17,551
Like I can't breathe.

266
00:36:19,887 --> 00:36:25,726
Every time I close my eyes,
I see Teacher Sam.

267
00:36:32,482 --> 00:36:35,068
Ma, take a look at Eli's drawings.

268
00:36:35,152 --> 00:36:36,612
They seem strange.

269
00:36:48,123 --> 00:36:49,625
Why would you scare him?

270
00:36:49,708 --> 00:36:53,253
Just tell them I did it.

271
00:37:02,429 --> 00:37:03,680
I did it.

272
00:37:03,764 --> 00:37:06,141
I pushed Teacher Sam.

273
00:37:07,935 --> 00:37:09,102
It hurts right here.

274
00:37:09,186 --> 00:37:10,771
I pushed Teacher Sam.

275
00:37:39,007 --> 00:37:40,092
Jackie.

276
00:37:44,972 --> 00:37:46,181
Anton…

277
00:37:55,273 --> 00:37:57,275
He was at the lighthouse…

278
00:38:02,322 --> 00:38:04,324
the night Sam died.

279
00:38:09,454 --> 00:38:10,539
Who?

280
00:38:13,875 --> 00:38:15,210
Eli.

281
00:38:32,185 --> 00:38:33,478
How…

282
00:38:36,231 --> 00:38:37,858
Did he see what happened?

283
00:38:42,404 --> 00:38:44,948
He accidentally pushed Sam.

284
00:39:06,428 --> 00:39:10,015
Let's trade tonight. Prepare the money.
But wait for my instructions.

285
00:39:14,561 --> 00:39:16,188
It doesn't matter who I am.

286
00:39:16,271 --> 00:39:17,981
I have Sam's phone and the secrets in it.

287
00:39:28,825 --> 00:39:30,285
Are you saying that…

288
00:39:32,496 --> 00:39:34,748
Anton gave money in exchange for this?

289
00:39:44,382 --> 00:39:48,303
Do you want me
out of your life that badly?

290
00:39:50,597 --> 00:39:52,557
You could get charged for this.

291
00:40:16,873 --> 00:40:18,291
How did you unlock this?

292
00:40:19,751 --> 00:40:21,586
I know someone who knows how.

293
00:40:22,879 --> 00:40:23,964
The…

294
00:40:25,298 --> 00:40:26,383
contents.

295
00:40:27,717 --> 00:40:29,427
Has anyone else seen them?

296
00:41:00,458 --> 00:41:01,626
You're right.

297
00:41:03,545 --> 00:41:05,213
You're right. Eli is innocent.

298
00:41:06,756 --> 00:41:08,842
He shouldn't face anything.

299
00:41:08,925 --> 00:41:10,093
He has nothing to admit.

300
00:41:12,137 --> 00:41:13,305
But why…

301
00:41:15,348 --> 00:41:16,641
Why does it feel…

302
00:41:18,226 --> 00:41:20,937
Something feels wrong, Anton.

303
00:41:24,065 --> 00:41:26,568
I don't understand.
I don't know what to do.

304
00:41:26,651 --> 00:41:28,320
I don't know what to do.

305
00:41:30,947 --> 00:41:33,825
It really was an accident, but…

306
00:41:38,121 --> 00:41:40,373
How are we going to tell people,

307
00:41:40,916 --> 00:41:42,209
tell everyone?

308
00:41:42,292 --> 00:41:44,336
What will happen to Eli?

309
00:41:44,419 --> 00:41:46,755
What about Eli?
What will happen to our kids?

310
00:41:46,838 --> 00:41:49,299
No one should know
about this, Jackie. No one.

311
00:41:50,217 --> 00:41:51,593
No one should ever know about this.

312
00:41:54,262 --> 00:41:55,597
Do you understand?

313
00:41:59,059 --> 00:42:00,644
Do you understand, Jackie?

314
00:43:08,461 --> 00:43:10,547
Did Mama tell you?

315
00:43:11,673 --> 00:43:12,966
Sorry.

316
00:43:15,468 --> 00:43:18,096
Only our family should know.

317
00:43:20,807 --> 00:43:22,225
Good day, Mr. Carpio.

318
00:43:22,309 --> 00:43:24,144
We'd like to invite you
to the police station.

319
00:43:24,227 --> 00:43:25,979
-What for?
-There's new evidence

320
00:43:26,062 --> 00:43:27,605
regarding Sam Ignacio's death.

321
00:43:27,689 --> 00:43:30,442
We've found Sam Ignacio's phone.

322
00:43:30,525 --> 00:43:33,361
I believe there are things
only you can shed light on.

323
00:43:33,445 --> 00:43:34,529
That's a nice story, Chief.

324
00:43:34,612 --> 00:43:36,740
The problem is, you have no evidence.

325
00:43:36,823 --> 00:43:40,952
This is from Sam's phone,
taken the night she died.

326
00:43:41,036 --> 00:43:45,623
When we first asked you
about the last time you saw Sam…

327
00:43:45,707 --> 00:43:47,542
It's true that Sam and I loved each other.

328
00:43:49,586 --> 00:43:50,420
Mrs. Carpio.

329
00:43:50,503 --> 00:43:52,255
Your son, Eli, is here at the lighthouse.

330
00:43:52,339 --> 00:43:54,132
I'll watch him until you get here.

331
00:43:54,215 --> 00:43:55,216
Oh, God, Eli.

332
00:43:57,510 --> 00:43:58,595
Hey!
